Students: test your computer coding skills in the Congressional App Challenge! Learn more, register, & submit your original app at  http://CongressionalAppChallenge.us . Deadline to submit is November 1st. If you have questions, call our office at 205.968.1290. 
#Congress4CS pic.twitter.com/CoiqZHDqlF
I have enjoyed serving Alabama in Congress alongside @RepMarthaRoby since my first day in office. I wish her and Riley the best and am confident she will do well in future endeavors.

Democrats just voted to raise the min wage to $15. This is economically unwise & hurts those it aims to help. According to CBO, a $15 min wage would mean: 
•3.7M jobs lost nationwide
•44,823 jobs lost in AL
•Entry jobs at risk of elimination
•$9B decrease of net family income pic.twitter.com/ZHGkeROq5I

Instead of wasting time debating Twitter comments, Congress should focus on addressing issues that are of greatest concern to Americans, including the crisis at the border. This is what we have been elected to do, not to be the social media police. https://palmer.house.gov/media-center/press-releases/palmer-vote-against-divisive-democrat-resolution …
Happy Independence Day! I hope you have an enjoyable holiday with your families celebrating our great nation. I'm thankful to be an American every day. #IndependenceDay2019 pic.twitter.com/T9Sqx1vogx

It was an honor to present a replica of the Office of Strategic Services (OSS) Congressional Gold Medal to Carillon Orban and Wendy Garner, daughter and granddaughter of Balazs “Bill” Orban, who served as a B-24 pilot with Operation Carpetbagger in World War II. #AL06 pic.twitter.com/nANdUbON39

Enjoyed touring the B'ham Fastener manufacturing plant, which employs over 175 people. The plant makes fasteners for industries like structural steel, water utilities, & transportation, & is the world’s largest producer of T-Head bolts. Special thanks to VP Kevin Johnson. #AL06 pic.twitter.com/maiv0qWiPM
